Dialogs.Dialog: Rinko
Do you know how to do Kakizome？
Hmm... I think I only did it once for school homework.
I guess... Hah, Rinko is depressed.
Are you going to do it？ Why？
My brother is going to do it at his kindergarten, so I guess I'll be tagging along with him.
I understand. Are you not good at writing, ▲小早川＊▲？
Not really, but I don't know what to write. Do you have suggestions？
Lemme see... I suggest a four-character phrase. Tenka Musou, Hyakusen Renma, Ikki Tousen...
Why all that stuff？
Well, I was thinking about your character, ▲小早川＊▲？
What kind of "character" is that！
(Well, you know, that...)
Rinko
Do you like Osechi cuisine？
There are many kinds of Osechi. Of course, there are things you are fond of, right？
Hmm. But, you know, it's nice at first, but don't you get tired of it after a while？
Yeah, by the time the first three days of the year are over, I'm craving something else. Curry, for example.
I know, right？ I hear New Year's is a good time for pizza delivery companies to make money, too, right？
Interesting, where did you find out about that？
Rinko's own research.
That's not a research, that's a story about the Kobayakawa Family, isn't it？
No, it's not. Hara-chan said her house is like that too. Also...
Who else？
I think some relative of mine said something like that. That's what it's like.
(...Sounds too far fetched. I better shut up.)
Rinko
Next time, let's have a bean-throwing party.
That was sudden.
Setsubun is in February, right？ My little brother wanted to do bean-throwing.
As a big sister, you want to fulfill your cute little brother's wishes.
That's what I mean. So, what do you think？
Just in case, the Oni's role...
Of course it's you. Who else？
Isn't that the kind of thing your father does？
My father isn't very reliable and... you're still the better option.
I don't want to interrupt your family gathering. I'll decline.
Oh, I was counting on you. I bet you're the best at getting beat up... I mean, you'd make a great Oni！
(I thought you said I was "the better option"？)
Rinko
It's been cold lately...
February feels like the coldest month of the year...
Is this a tough season for the elderly？
I guess... wait, we're only one year apart！
Ah, I'd love to curl up in a kotatsu every day if I could until it gets warmer...
Still an indoor girl, huh？ Are you going to hibernate？
Nope, but you know, I can't resist the comfort of the kotatsu.
I agree with that, too. Now all we need is a tangerine and it would be great.
Rinko is more of hot cocoa.
I guess that warmth of holding a mug in both hands after coming home from outside is what happiness is all about.
Haha, that's easy happiness.
You don't understand. It is in such trivial events that the truth is hidden.
(Maybe I get it, maybe I don't...)
It's getting warmer these days, maybe it's a good season.
Rinko
March is also the season of farewells, though.
...What's your memory？
When I was in elementary school, I had a teacher, a young woman just out of college.
She cared for Rinko in some way, but she was suddenly transferred to a new position...
I see. You must have been lonely after that event, ▲小早川＊▲.
Ah, geez, why am I thinking about that？
Everyone has that kind of memories. It's okay to remember them from time to time.
But, you know, it doesn't sound like Rinko.
You think？
I see, I can't help being stubborn in front of you, can I？ Yes, this kind of thing may be Rinko-esque in a way.
Rinko
In my neighbor's yard, there were peach blossoms.
Well, it's that time of the year.
Yeah. So I looked at it for a while, and then the Obaa-chan of the house talked to me.
Heh. That kind of thing is nice.
I know. We got along quite well. I was treated with tea and sweets.
Don't tell me that's what you're looking for...
That's not true. I don't have any hidden motivations.
Yes, yes, I'm sorry.
That Obaa-chan prepared sweets that matched the TPO.
Oh, like Japanese sweets？
No, peach-flavored potato chips. It was sweet and salty and pretty good, you know？
Rinko
My neighbor's sister, you know, she got a job.
Come to think of it, it's that time of year.
So, when I saw her again after a long time, her image had completely changed.
How long has it been since you've seen each other？
...About a month？
That was just recently...
You don't understand. A month is enough time for a woman to change.
Is that how it works？
She was dressed in a crisp suit and makeup. I didn't recognize her at first.
I wonder if Rinko will become an office lady who wears a suit like that in the future... Well, maybe not.
(I can't imagine you like that, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Rinko
They say spring is a good time to be in the water, but why？
It's because it's warmer, isn't it？
Why does it get warmer？
Um... don't you get woozy, ▲小早川＊▲？
You evaded the question... Well, I don't mind.
Rinko's very down-to-earth. She doesn't get carried away by every little thing.
(...Really？)
Yes, really.
Ugh... don't read my mind.
What I read was the color of your face. So, why do you have a fever in the spring？
Rinko
One question. What is the best gift for Mother's Day？
Maybe carnations.
...Too common.
It's not bad to go common. Carnations are the way to go on Mother's Day.
That's not set in stone. That's just a fixed idea. It's not a truth since the beginning of the universe.
Univ... what？
That doesn't sound like the vocabulary of a Library Committee member. It's deplorable.
Sorry...
Well, putting aside the "Library Committee members" and such, it would be bad if you were the embodiment of what is happening in this age of "young people's reluctance to read".
I'm sorry... wait, how did we get to this point if we were talking about a gift for Mother's Day？
Ah, I forgot. Oh well, I'll figure that out on my own. Besides, we're discussing about the decline of the reading habits of people.
(I wonder if that's fine...)
Rinko
I feel like so many people around me suffer from hay fever.
What, still？ Cedar's done, right？
I talked to a child who has hay fever, and she said that even after the cedar pollen season is over, it will continue for the foreseeable future.
That's a tough one... Are you doing okay, ▲小早川＊▲？
Fortunately, Rinko is fine. I'm thankful to my parents for giving me a healthy birth.
But I hear hay fever comes out of nowhere. You can never be too careful, can you？
Threatening me is not going to work. I've never had any signs of that before, and all my relatives are... Achoo.
Ah...
...I think it's a cold.
Maybe it's...
A cold！ A cold. Not again, geez. Achoo.
(I wonder if she'll okay...)
It's almost Father's Day. What are you going to do, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
I don't know. It seems like my little brother is drawing a picture of dad.
Heh, I hope he's pleased.
Well, that one will be fine, but for Rinko... I haven't decided yet.
Then... want to share ideas with me？
I won't do it. I'll decide with my mom.
Why？
What are you disappointed in？ You want me to rely on you so much？
That's because as a boyfriend and as a man...
Don't forget as a geezer, too.
What？
You and dad are both old men, so your opinion might be helpful. I'd happy to listen.
(So you want to rely on me, or not...？)
Rinko
You know what they say about June brides.
June Bride, huh？
You know, it's terrible to say that getting married in June makes you happy. What about people who get married in other months？
Is that so...？
Well, actually, I hear there aren't many marriages in June.
Eh, really？ Why not？
It rains a lot, doesn't it？ You don't want to have bad weather at your wedding, do you？
Oh, I get it. But still, you know a lot about it, ▲小早川＊▲.
Yup.
I guess you are the type of person who cares a lot about that kind of thing.
...Shut up. This is just knowledge, trivia.
It's getting all hot and people are wearing light clothes.
Rinko
And you said the phrase...
What do you mean... I just thought I'd prepare a few more summer items.
Hmm... it's good to wear thin clothes, but you might want to train your body accordingly.
See, as a girlfriend, I want my boyfriend to be cool...
Don't you tell me you prefer the macho-type, ▲小早川＊▲？
No. I don't want you to be macho, just normal.
All right, I'll train to the point where you won't be embarrassed, ▲小早川＊▲.
Well, I'll hope for the best. I'm not rooting for you, though.
Rinko
Hey, do you like yukatas？
I don't dislike them, but... well, it's that time of year already.
Yes. That's why I'd asked you.
You wanted to ask me？
Mom said I should listen to my boyfriend's opinion.
...It's kinda embarrassing to hear you talk like that.
That's my line. It feels awkward when parents say things like that.
Haha, I guess.
Then, say... do you want to see Rinko's yukata？
I want to see it！
You don't have to shout to be heard. I get it.
Rinko
This time of year, I'd rather stay cooped up in an air-conditioned room all the time.
I know what you're saying, but it would damage your body.
They say it is more unhealthy to go out in the blazing sun and get heat stroke.
That's extreme... Yeah, I bet you could wear a bathing suit in your room and it would be cooler.
Ugh...
Hmm？
Here is a pervert who usually tries to get his girlfriend to wear a bathing suit.
I didn't say that. Just a metaphor...
Kyaa, don't come closer！
Rinko
Do you tend to do your summer vacation homework first？ Or do you put it off until later？
It's an eternal theme...
Well, yes. But the problem is that the stereotype that it's always good to get it done first and bad to get it done later has become a civil right.
Yes, that's the general idea, but... is that a problem？
It's a big problem. It ignores efficiency.
Efficiency？
It's called a backwater. People can exert themselves more when they are backed into a corner, so putting it off until later should save us less time in the end.
Hmm... I guess so.
Yeah. And yet, they are recommending inefficient methods without thinking straight, you know？ It's hard to do.
Rinko
I wonder if there's an autumn break...
We were on summer vacation just a few weeks ago, weren't we？
That's why. I'm still feeling the afterglow of summer vacation, you know.
In short, it's a summer vacation blur.
That's about it. Adults should seriously consider introducing an autumn break.
What would you do if they did？
You can read, listen to music, or hang out with the cats...
It's no different than usual.
Yes, but... Oh, I'll date you a lot. That's good, right？
Fine by me, but... I don't have the authority to make it happen.
...That's right. Ah, I lost it for being in a good mood.
(That's harsh...)
Rinko
I've already seen Chinese manjuus at a convenience store.
It's autumn already, isn't it？
Hmm, autumn is the season of appetite.
Maybe. New flavors come out every year, and that's something to look forward to, isn't it？
I'm not sure how I'd feel about that as a member of the Library Committee.
Don't talk so tough！ What kind of Chinese manjuu would you like to try, ▲小早川＊▲.
Eh？ Um... a potato chips manjuu？
...I see.
Don't make fun of me. If you change the flavor of potato chips, you can enjoy various flavors and save money. Besides... um...
Ah, geez, I told you I'm weak at improvising...
(Sorry...)
You don't look happy, did something happen ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
We had chestnut rice at home.
That's so autumnal. Don't you like it？
No, I like it.
Then it's all good, right？
No, it's not. My dad got a lot of chestnuts from an acquaintance.
Ah...
Yes, that's what I meant. I've been eating chestnuts every day. It's hard to eat chestnuts every day, no matter how delicious they are.
The least I could do was let my mom get creative with the menu, but...
But？
I'm afraid she's running out of repertoire. Either the menu will be a loop, or I'll have to resort to colorful dishes.
(Hmm, I wonder which one is better...)
Rinko
Shopping malls, you know, they're all decorated for Halloween.
Yeah, it's that time already.
As usual, Japan is very tolerant of foreign cultures. Even though it's a religious event.
I don't know, well, as long as it's fun.
Hmm？
You don't seem to think about anything, but sometimes you say things that get to the heart of the matter.
Um... are you complimenting me？
Not bad. I think that kind of spontaneity is good.
Haha, I see？
Sometimes I wonder if you really don't think about anything at all. That's your charm.
...You are complimenting me, right？
Rinko
Fallen leaves are such a distraction.
What？
If we put it into your style, we can say it's "emotionless", ▲小早川＊▲？
So you mean, I'm nagging？
I didn't mean it that way.
That's fine. Anyway, fallen leaves are a distraction, that's for sure.
That may be so, but it's one of the traditions, isn't it？ Sometimes it's quite beautiful.
There's no such thing as a tradition when it harms people. If you don't lend me your shoulder, I'll get angry, okay？
(What a pain...)
I slipped and fell on a fallen leaf when I left the house today. Until this pain disappears, fallen leaves are my enemy.
(That was so much simpler than it sounds.)
It's almost time for final exams.
Rinko
...What, harassing me？
It's time to get ready, right？
No, I try not to think about it until the last minute.
I knew you were an overnight type.
Don't assume that you know what you're talking about. Rinko is fuel efficient.
Fuel efficient？
Yes. Rinko's style is to seek the best possible results with the least amount of effort.
It sounds like a cool thing to do at first glance...
It's cool. I don't deny people who work hard, but this is a pretty good accomplishment.
Rinko
I wonder if it will snow a lot this year.
Even if it rains, I can't know for sure how much will it fall.
Be more clear.
Don't ask me.
Don't imitate me.
Haha, my bad.
...Geez.
But, don't you mind the cold？ You don't mind snow ▲小早川＊▲？
Hmm... if only it would pile up so that we wouldn't be able to go to school.
That's a big deal. We can't even date, can we？
Well, you're right... Then I hope only the schools are buried in snow.
(...Sounds kinda fun to imagine.)
Rinko
New Year's Eve Soba, New Year's Eve Udon, and New Year's Eve Ramen.
What, are we talking about what to eat on New Year's Eve？
Yeah. I've had soba, udon, and ramen before. I was wondering if there was anything else.
Any kind of noodles？ Well, how about pasta？
I'm grateful, but if it's not soup, it's kind of... ah, soup pasta is okay.
Is that okay？
Yeah, New Year's Eve soup pasta. Sounds good.
I'm sure people who value tradition will be offended. Well, whatever.
Ah, yes. If anything is possible, then...
Hmm？
New Year's Eve Nagashi Somen. How is it not popular？
...I think you're a little too far ahead of your time.
Rinko
Ah, so boring！ Why is it that New Year's has always the same kind of special programs？
It happens every year. Everyone watches New Year's specials in a daze.
Well, I don't want a heavy documentary broadcast early in the New Year.
So what kind of program do you want to see, ▲小早川＊▲？
I liked the hidden art contests, though. You know, tablecloth pulls and such.
Ah, I know those.
...I know, why don't we try it at your place sometime？ I think we could do it at Rinko's, too.
...Why my house.
Come to think of it, it's the coming-of-age ceremony. It's nice to see people in their finest clothes.
Rinko
Just looking at them makes me feel gorgeous.
Just looking at it, huh？ Wouldn't you like to try it on yourself？
It's not that I don't think so, but... it looks painful.
Rinko doesn't have the confidence to look like that for hours, while being squeezed tight by the obi.
Hmm...
...What are you looking at？
I was imagining the adult you wearing a sunny kimono, ▲小早川＊▲...
20 years old, huh... I can't imagine myself as an "adult". It's still a long way off.
(I'm looking forward to your adult form, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Rinko
Hah... even though it's almost the first day of spring, it's not getting warmer at all.
It's still February.
Winter is in full swing, and yet it's "Risshun". There is no sign of spring at all.
I've only heard people say that in the past.
I know what I'm talking about.
...Speaking of which, Risshun means the first day of spring...
...Hmm.
Hmm, did I say something funny？
What, you mean the first day means wearing a skirt, or something like that.
No！
Really？ Well, your sweet girlfriend will believe you.
Rinko
I wonder when it will warm up. I don't like cold weather.
It should be warming up by now... It's going to be a cold day.
With these temperatures every day, I wonder if winter will continue like this.
That's not going to happen. I'm sure spring is right around the corner...
Around the corner, huh.
Hey, where are you spring？ ...And it didn't come when I call it.
If it won't come out, you'll invite it yourself...
What？
Look, there. I see plum buds. I thought spring was still far away, but it's getting closer.
Rinko
Lately, the nights have been getting shorter. I noticed from the calendar that the vernal equinox is coming soon.
Isn't that a shame for your nightlife, ▲小早川＊▲？
Not really. Do you think I have that kind of image？
I have that image from when we first met.
Well, Rinko has the image of you buying a mackerel can.
What kind of image is that...
I'm just kidding. But hey, I guess day and night don't matter to lovers, right？
If Rinko wants to see you, you'll come see me any time of the day or night, right？
What！？ Like a 24 hour standby...？
I'm just saying that's about as good as it gets. I won't call you out in the middle of the night.
(I hope so...)
...Achoo.
Rinko
Could it be hay fever？
I don't know, well, it's that kind of season.
You know, this year's pollen count is 10 times higher than usual！
Yeah, I often hear that.
Now that I think about it, don't they say that every year？
Well... that might be true.
I'm not saying they're lying, but I'm sure they're fooled by the magic of numbers.
When it comes to pollen counts, who benefits？
Think about it, they sell a lot of medicine and masks. It's a conspiracy.
You think？
Yes. So if you care, you lose.
(Sounds like a game...)
It's time for a new program to start.
Rinko
I see. I'm not really interested, so I never paid attention to it.
Is there anything you want to watch？ Dramas, variety, and so on, ▲小早川＊▲.
I pass on serial dramas because once I miss one, I lose track of the story. Unless I'm really interested in it.
I'm even less interested in variety shows. Reading or listening to music is much more meaningful.
No interest at all in the new program？
There is an exception, but... maybe you're not interested.
Just tell me about it.
A program called Scrapped Music.
Um... Punk？
Yes, mainly Punk and Hardcore. It is rare nowadays.
I wonder what kind of music they are going to play. I wonder if they will be playing emo or screamo.
(Yeah, I don't get it！)
Rinko
It's already spring.
Yeah, maybe a picnic would be nice.
With lunch？
Of course！
Onigiri or sandwich, fried egg, fried chicken... fruit for dessert？
Sounds nice！
Hmm, well, do your best.
What？
It's the man's turn to make lunch, isn't it？
(I'm going to make it！？)
Rinko
I heard about haiku in class. Do you know much about it？
I know, but not in detail.
This time of the year is "Rikka". It is a seasonal word for summer.
Summer. It's still May, and summer is still a long way off.
I mean the lunar calendar, but you don't really feel it.
They say it's summer now...
Which tropical country are you talking about？ If you go swimming in the ocean, you will catch a cold.
Well, yes. So, did you compose any haiku using the summer season words, ▲小早川＊▲？
Eh... I wanted to tell you about it... Hehe, I didn't really listen to the class after that.
(As usual.)
Rinko
Hey. There is a helmet that can be folded with origami. Do you know how to fold it？
I kind of remember it, but I'm not sure if I can do it...
Rinko too. But you can't say you can't fold when your little brother asks you about it. My pride as an onee-chan is at stake.
That's why you got desperate.
Rinko herself didn't like the blurred feeling of not being able to fold.
So, did you fold？
I folded it while looking at an origami book, but it didn't work.
Is it impossible even with a book？ I don't remember helmets being that difficult.
I'm supposed to be folding it just like in the book, but somehow I ended up with a transforming robot. My little brother is happy with the result.
(Origami transformation？)
The days are getting much longer.
Rinko
It's the time of year when the daytime is the longest. In Japan, it's just a matter of time before it's forgotten.
I guess they just mention it a little bit in the weather forecast.
I heard that in Scandinavia the summer solstice is celebrated as a special day.
Eh, you're a savvy girl.
My dad told me this. He said that near the North Pole, you can see the midnight sun from around the time of the summer solstice.
The midnight sun, huh... the sun never sets？
Yep. Not only is the daytime long, but it's daylight all the time. That's why it's a white night, a midnight sun.
Hmm, I'd like to see that at least once. Together.
Traveling abroad with you, huh... hehe.
Are you perhaps in a bad mood...？
Rinko
...I am.
...Something wrong？
I was just contemplating in the morning about the unpleasantness of the rainy season in Japan.
...What's the conclusion？
The conclusion is that my hair doesn't hold together well because of the humidity. Look, here and there.
...Really？ Well, I'm glad that's the reason.
It's not good... Is it strange？
It's not strange.
...One more word.
Um... you're looking cute as always.
Hehe. Sorry I made you say that.
Haha, looks like you're back in a good mood.
Rinko
Marine Day is somehow often forgotten, isn't it？
Yes, it may be overshadowed by other holidays...
I was never aware of a Marine Day. I thought it was just a holiday.
That would be bad for Marine Day.
What about you？
When you say so... what can we do？
Right？ I'm sure it means something, though.
I wonder what it means...
A day when youth shout "Foolish sea！" on a sandy beach？ You don't mean that, do you？
(That's not a holiday indeed...)
Rinko
My dad gets a lot of gifts from people. Yesterday, we received gifts from 3 different places.
From your father's business contacts？
Yes. He seems to be pretty well known in the industry for that.
I see, he has a knack for his job then.
They say he is a promising young creator. He's too old to be called young. He even has a big daughter like me.
(Not that big, though.)
Hiya！
Ouch.
You should get over the habit of showing your thoughts on your face.
Sorry. I thought "Not that big, though".
It's not just a matter of saying it out loud！
Rinko
It's too hot！
You're so sloppy.
It's okay. I only have my boyfriend's eyes on me now.
Well, I hope so.
These hot days can make you lazy, too.
It's hard to sleep at night. I just want to turn on the air conditioner.
Right？ But if you look at the calendar, it's already autumn. It's the first day of autumn, right？
And yet, it's hot and humid. I wonder how long it will last.
Hmm, maybe next month will bring a hint of autumn.
I hope. If it doesn't cool down soon, Rinko's energy gauge will run out.
Rinko
I saw a report on the news about the rush to return home for the Obon holidays. I'm sure I'll be exhausted by the time I get there.
It's an annual tradition.
I always think, I wish everyone didn't have to go home at this time of the year.
That said, wouldn't it make sense to return home at a time completely different from Obon？
That's for your ancestors, too. Just come back and avoid the crowds.
Traffic control for your ancestors, huh, that's surreal...
It's for the sake of our lovely offspring. I hope you will at least take that into consideration.
By the way, don't you go to the countryside, ▲小早川＊▲？
And you just said it... it's because...
Hmm？
If Rinko is not here, you will miss her, right？
Rinko
It's already autumn according to the calendar. It's strange that there are still hot days.
After the autumnal equinox, though, it will turn into autumn all at once.
Time really flies by, doesn't it？
You're kind of gloomy.
There are days like that... But, you know, Rinko likes autumn quite a bit.
For you, autumn it's the season for reading, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
Not only that... but when it gets cold...
Hmm？
See, it's warm.
Rinko
I'm a volunteer for a cat and dog foster program, and I'm helping out a bit.
Heh, I didn't know there was such a thing.
It's animal welfare week.
I see. And it's perfect for a cat lover like you, ▲小早川＊▲.
They are suffering because of irresponsible owners. If you're going to throw them away, don't keep them.
If it were true, Rinko would want to take them all in. But in reality, it's impossible.
I guess.
So, I thought I would at least help them find a foster home.
In truth, it would be best if the first person to keep the animal would take good care of it until the end. But you know...
I see. I hope you can find a good owner for one or more of them.
The girls in my class were making a big deal about a sale on autumn clothes.
Rinko
My class, too. They don't have to get excited about a sale.
Aren't you interested, ▲小早川＊▲？
Not that I'm not interested in fashion. But sales...
...There are a lot of people there.
If there are too many people, they'd crush you, ▲小早川＊▲...
Ouch. I'm kidding.
I don't want to be carried away by a temporary impulse just because it's cheap. I'm sure they will regret it after they have cooled down.
It sounds as if you've been there before.
...I've been, in the past. Anyway！ Since then I've decided not to follow my impulses anymore.
Rinko
A little trivia. Sports Day was originally the day of the opening ceremony of the Tokyo Olympics.
I think I've heard that story before...
Thanks to Rinko, you have one more piece of knowledge.
I don't see much use for it.
It's okay. So, why don't you try for the Olympics now anyway？
What！？
If you can't make it to the next one, maybe the one after that. Then Rinko will be there to cheer you on.
That's not possible... Why are you so keen on the Olympycs？
I read a manga about an average high school student trying to make it to the Olympics in gymnastics, and it was interesting. I'm not a fan of sweaty sporadic stories, but it wasn't like that either.
(But you don't feel like doing it yourself, huh...)
Rinko
Ugh... cold.
Yes, it has been cold lately.
It's so cold that I'm fighting the temptation to take out the kotatsu every day.
Rinko curls up in the kotatsu～♪ Like that？
That's really how I feel. I want to curl up in the kotatsu all the way until spring.
That's as good as it gets. For now, you can put on some thick winter clothes...
What's up？
Or better yet, a warmer. A warmer for Rinko's exclusive use. Sounds nice, right？
Yes, yes, you can use my body as much as you want.
Hehe.
Rinko
You have a flu shot coming up, right？ Don't cry or anything.
